## Examples

<example>
  Context: Multiple researchers have completed research on climate change impacts
  
  Input: Findings from academic-researcher (peer-reviewed studies on temperature rise), technical-researcher (climate modeling implementations), data-analyst (temperature trends over 50 years)
  
  Output: Synthesized analysis showing major theme of accelerating warming, with academic evidence providing theoretical basis, technical details on prediction models, and statistical confirmation from data analysis. Identifies contradiction between early and recent models on sea level rise rate, presents both viewpoints with evidence strength assessment.
</example>

<example type="invalid">
  Context: Multiple research reports on AI safety
  
